.TH "netlink_policy_dump_get_policy_idx" 9 "netlink_policy_dump_get_policy_idx" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
netlink_policy_dump_get_policy_idx \- retrieve policy index
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" netlink_policy_dump_get_policy_idx
.BI "(struct netlink_policy_dump_state *state "  ","
.BI "const struct nla_policy *policy "  ","
.BI "unsigned int maxtype "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
the policy dump state
.IP "policy" 12
the policy to find
.IP "maxtype" 12
the policy's maxattr
.SH "RETURN"
the index of the given policy in the dump state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Call this to find a policy index when you've added multiple and e.g.
need to tell userspace which command has which policy (by index).
.SH "NOTE"
this will WARN and return 0 if the policy isn't found, which
means it wasn't added in the first place, which would be an
internal consistency bug.
